cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Trusted-Loop Mode in your research or tooling, please cite it."
title: "Trusted-Loop Mode: Evidence-Grounded Completion Gating for Unattended AI Coding Agents"
abstract: >-
  A Claude Code plugin and multi-agent framework that keeps an unattended AI
  coding agent working until an independent ensemble of LLM judges confirms the
  task is complete. Completion is verified against fresh behavioral evidence
  (test/build/lint output, tool results, diffs) re-gathered at stop time and a
  fixed definition of done — not the agent's own claim of completion. Judges run
  independently and in parallel for decorrelation; aggregation is by evidence,
  not votes (a confident, evidence-cited "incomplete" blocks; an evidence-free
  objection does not). Hard caps, stuck-detection, and fail-open-on-error make
  unattended runs safe, and every decision is logged to an eval dataset.
type: software
